==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[enuntiatus]]'', past participle of ''[[enuntiare]]'' to report, declare, from e- + ''[[nuntiare]]'' to report 

===Pronunciation===
*IPA: /ɪˈnʌnsiˌeɪt/

===Hyphenation===
e·nun·ci·ate

===Verb===
{{en-verb|enunciat|ing}}

# {{transitive}}: To make a definite or systematic statement of.
# To [[announce]], proclaim.
#:''The boss '''enunciated''' the new policy.''
# To [[articulate]], [[pronounce]].
#:''You must '''enunciate''' all the syllables.''

